The paper deals with interference mitigation in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Signal Processing (cs.SI), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on the capacity region of a two-user Gaussian interference channel with conferencing transmitters, it is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because they deal with aspects of wireless networks and signal processing, but they are less likely to be the primary focus of the paper.
